abstract: BALTIMORE, Sept. 30. -- The break to 170 by Atlantic Coast Line common, followed by a partial recovery, was the most notable feature of to-day's trading. The break was ascribed to a forced sale at the market, which fell into the selling at the most inopportune moment. It was offered about the time Louisville and Nashville was looking its ugliest, hence the indisposition to buy except at a wide concession.

abstract: PRINCETON, N.J., Oct. 1 -- Princeton defeated Swarthmore here to-day in the opening football game of the season by a score of 18 to 0. A brilliant run of Hart's and McClave's centre dive scored the first touch-down after eighteen minutes' play.

abstract: BOSTON, Oct. 3. -- New York's baseball team lost both games of the double-header played here to-day. The local men won the first game with heavy hitting in the third inning, during which they scored six times on a base on balls, an error, and five hits. abstract: PRINCETON, N.J., Oct. 4 -- Princeton defeated Lehigh's football team here to-day by a score of 23 to 0. Princeton's strong defense kept the ball in Lehigh's territory through the same, but the offense was so weak in the opening half that no score could be made. At one time the ball was pushed thirty yards down the field, but a confusion of signals on Lehigh's one-yard line lost the ball.

abstract: Messrs. abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 14. -- There was no marked improvement in the local market to-day, notwithstanding the favorable turn in the coal strike situation. Prices improved fractionally, but the average net gain of the active stocks was less than one-half of 1 per cent. There were two reasons for this hesitancy: First, some apprehension that the miners might not consent to the operators' plan, and second, to a continued scarcity of loanable funds.

abstract: BALTIMORE, Oct. 15. - -The tightness in the money market is also the continuing feature of the securities market. The general tone of the latter market is better, but traders are unable to secure funds to take advantage of the improvement. abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 18 -- The conspicuous feature in an otherwise narrow market was United Gas Improvement stock, which was traded in to the extent of 2,462 shares. abstract: THE last few days have been crowded with weddings and, naturally, the chief interest, so far as dress costuming is concerned, has been in bridal gowns. abstract: ANNAPOLIS, Md., Oct. 18 -- The Lehigh and the Navat Academy football teams played a tie game here this afternoon, each side scoring a touch-down. Lehigh scored in the first half on a spectacular run of 95 yards by A. Farabaugh. Annapolis scored in an unusual manner. Belknap punted from Lehigh's 35-yard line and the ball bounded and rolled for quite a distance behind the gpal line, where Whiting of the Navy fell on it.

abstract: CHICAGO, Oct. 22. -- New York exchange to-day was quoted at 3O cents discount: time and call loans 6 per cent. Local stocks were beset with dullness save in spots. Box Board felt somewhat buoyant over the bond conversion plan on foot for the preferred stock, and that issue made good advances on small trading.

abstract: Only two of the larger college football teams played games yesterday, Princeton winning from Dickinson by a score of 23 to 0, and Pennsylvania losing to Annapolis by 6 to 10. abstract: LONDON, Oct. 25. -- King Edward and Queen Alexandra started on the royal progress toward the city shortly after noon today in somewhat dull weather. abstract: LONDON, Oct. 27. -- The present inordinate cost of living is exercising a paralyzing effect at Johannesburg, says The Times's correspondent in that city. abstract: BALTIMORE, Oct. 27 -- The strong recovering tendency shown by some of the Cotton Duck issues was the main feature of to-day's market. They have been unduly depressed of late as the result of a misapprehension as to what the company is accomplishing. There have been efforts among shorts to hold them down in order to cover sales made under a false notion as to what the company would do in July.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 27 -- Little comment can be made on to-day's local market. Its chief characteristic was extreme dullness, the sales amounting to $15,644 shares and $19,275 bonds. In Consolidated Lake Superior, Philadelphia Rapid Transit, Philadelphia Company, and Philadelphia Electric there was evidence of pool buying, but the remainder of the list was without feature.

abstract: MEMPHIS, Oct. 30 -- The Fall meeting of the Memphis Trotting Association closed to-day. To-morrow at a matinee, Cresceus will trot against his record, and Dan Patch and Prince Alert, pacers, will try for marks at a mile. To-day the majority of the races were dashes for beaten horses. Lord Derby trotted against the world's record, 2:02 1/4, but was timed in 2:06 1/4.
